---
name: scljet-write-index-composite
description: SclJet composite (multi-column) index — an index B-tree keyed on two columns that reference SQLite validates and uses (cross-backend)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet composite index

[ByteSlice, byteSliceToList, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableWithIndexDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)

```scalascript
// A two-column index on (a, b). Entries are [a, b, rowid] records sorted
// lexicographically by (a, b, rowid). Reference integrity_check validates the
// index and the planner uses it for `a=? AND b=?`. int and JS agree.
val rows = List(
  List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlInteger(10L), SqlText("p")),
  List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlInteger(20L), SqlText("q")),
  List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlInteger(5L), SqlText("r")),
  List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlInteger(10L), SqlText("s")),
  List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlInteger(10L), SqlText("t")))

buildTableWithIndexDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(a INTEGER, b INTEGER, v TEXT)",
  "comp", "CREATE INDEX comp ON t(a, b)", List(0, 1), rows) match
  case Right(bytes) => println((bytes.length / 512).toString + ":" + byteSliceToList(bytes).toString)
  case Left(error) => println("ERROR:" + error.message)
```
